WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:05.474
you're listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.279 --> 00:10.021
If I haven't met you yet, my name is Jeremy.

00:10.061 --> 00:11.484
I'm one of the elders here.

00:11.544 --> 00:17.874
And today is a very special day for us because today is Vision Sunday.

00:17.934 --> 00:19.737
Are you excited for Vision Sunday?

00:19.797 --> 00:20.718
Yes.

00:21.499 --> 00:30.834
We do this every year to discover God's vision for our church and to align around it as we seek the renewal of Los Angeles through the good news of Jesus.

00:31.042 --> 00:38.314
And this is so important because the norm for every institution, organization, or church is vision drift.

00:38.855 --> 00:46.909
You see, gradually over time, what happens is that churches slowly veer away from who God has called them to be.

00:46.929 --> 00:56.946
And so as a church, we have to recognize that we will never drift into faithfulness to Jesus, especially not in a city like Los Angeles.

00:57.218 --> 01:05.669
So we have to be clear about who God has called us to be and then commit to it and then recommit over and over again.

01:05.709 --> 01:09.154
And the same is actually true for you as an individual.

01:09.575 --> 01:12.819
You will never drift into Christ likeness.

01:13.440 --> 01:16.804
You will not wander into maturity or holiness.

01:17.485 --> 01:23.954
You have to deliberately seek God's vision for your life and then build everything around it.

01:24.418 --> 01:28.343
And I know that you've got your individual goals and your New Year's resolutions.

01:28.923 --> 01:33.689
But what you need is to be a part of a community that has clear direction from God.

01:34.350 --> 01:37.273
And that is what Vision Sunday is all about.

01:37.874 --> 01:41.278
So what we're going to do today is answer four questions.

01:41.999 --> 01:42.539
Who are we?

01:43.320 --> 01:44.061
Where have we been?

01:44.121 --> 01:45.683
Where are we going?

01:45.703 --> 01:48.306
And what's my part?

01:49.538 --> 01:56.508
Now, if you're visiting here today, this is a perfect day for you to be here, because you're really good to see who we are and what we're all about as a church.

01:57.189 --> 02:08.666
And if you're a member of this church, this is a critical time every year where we unite around God's vision and then recommit to Christ, to one another, and to the mission that He's given us in this city.

02:09.327 --> 02:16.337
Now, we'll look at a lot of Scripture throughout this, and I will preach a text in the middle of it, but let's just begin with a word of prayer.

02:16.537 --> 02:17.298
Okay, pray with me.

02:18.850 --> 02:24.757
God, we come before you today, expectant, because we believe that you are the living God.

02:25.919 --> 02:32.107
We are not just looking back at a historical figure, but we believe that Christ is risen.

02:32.207 --> 02:34.029
He's on the move in this city.

02:34.089 --> 02:39.636
We believe that you work in different ways and different generations and different cities.

02:39.756 --> 02:46.004
And God, we want what you would have for us as a church here in Los Angeles.

02:46.945 --> 02:47.666
And God,

02:48.098 --> 02:50.262
This time just feels so critical.

02:50.302 --> 02:55.370
I mean, the world is so unstable right now, and yet you are stable.

02:55.630 --> 02:57.674
You are our stability.

02:58.976 --> 03:07.409
And Lord, as we look forward into 2026, we have to acknowledge that we don't know everything that's going to come.

03:08.171 --> 03:12.317
In fact, we can expect the unexpected in so many ways.

03:12.417 --> 03:15.282
We don't know what's going to happen in this year.

03:15.490 --> 03:18.576
But God, we know that you will be faithful in all of it.

03:19.398 --> 03:22.044
We know that you won't be surprised by any of it.

03:22.725 --> 03:29.960
And we know that you will be at work in every single way of building your kingdom, of drawing us closer to yourself.

03:30.040 --> 03:34.610
So today, Lord, would you help us to see you for who you are?

03:35.042 --> 03:47.261
to get a clear sense of where you're leading us as a congregation, and then for us to unite around that and commit to it, with a desperation that says, if the Lord doesn't move, then we will fall flat on our faces.

03:47.622 --> 03:49.444
You're all we have, God, you're all we want.

03:49.925 --> 03:51.147
Would you lead us in this time?

03:51.207 --> 03:54.693
We pray this in Jesus' name, amen, amen.

03:55.394 --> 03:57.717
All right, so four questions, and the first is this.

03:58.158 --> 04:00.722
Who are we as a church?

04:00.962 --> 04:01.803
We are a church.

04:01.964 --> 04:06.030
We are a community of broken people who are being made new by Jesus.

04:06.611 --> 04:11.238
And our name is Reality Church of Los Angeles or Reality LA for short.

04:11.859 --> 04:14.583
And some people hear that and they think, why is your name reality?

04:15.083 --> 04:17.467
Like, that's kind of an odd name for a church.

04:17.667 --> 04:20.612
Well, it actually comes from the Bible, okay?

04:21.053 --> 04:29.906
In Colossians 2, Paul is talking about all the things that people look to for meaning and identity and purpose, but in the end, they're only shadows.

04:30.242 --> 04:34.347
Then in verse 17 of Colossians 2, it lands with the real weight.

04:34.387 --> 04:38.111
He says this, these are a shadow of the things that were to come.

04:38.672 --> 04:42.877
The reality, however, is found in Christ.

04:43.598 --> 04:49.685
So that's why our church is called reality LA, because we believe that Jesus is reality.

04:50.086 --> 04:52.168
He's the one who fulfills our longings.

04:52.328 --> 04:54.171
He's the one who heals our wounds.

04:54.471 --> 04:57.074
He's the one who forgives our sin.

04:57.538 --> 05:04.329
And then when community is built around Jesus, we can actually be real with one another.

05:04.950 --> 05:09.277
We don't have to hide behind the facade of religious performance or career success.

05:09.958 --> 05:12.162
We don't have to pretend to have it all together.

05:12.763 --> 05:15.127
We're all broken and Jesus is making us new.

05:15.167 --> 05:22.038
And so that's why our vision is seeking the renewal of Los Angeles through the good news of Jesus.

05:22.880 --> 05:24.402
And I know that a lot of churches

05:24.578 --> 05:30.886
posture themselves against the city, kind of in us versus them, but we are for the city.

05:31.326 --> 05:35.352
We love Los Angeles because Jesus loves Los Angeles.

05:35.952 --> 05:43.382
And we long to see the lost save, the lonely brought into community, and the city of angels become more like the kingdom of God.

05:44.243 --> 05:46.966
But what's our role in that renewal?

05:47.026 --> 05:50.130
As we seek renewal, what are we supposed to do?

05:50.402 --> 05:53.506
Well, Jesus was clear on our mission.

05:53.526 --> 05:58.672
He said, go therefore and make disciples of all nations.

05:59.393 --> 06:08.004
So the mission of the church is not to draw a crowd, but to make disciples, people who know him and learn from him and become like him over a lifetime.

06:08.905 --> 06:13.671
And then Jesus says, we do this by teaching them to observe all that I commanded.

06:14.391 --> 06:19.698
And so for us as a church, we break that down by saying that our mission is to make disciples

06:19.842 --> 06:24.307
who follow Jesus, love one another, and serve Los Angeles.

06:24.988 --> 06:25.869
That's what we're about.

06:26.229 --> 06:27.711
That's what we're obsessed with.

06:27.931 --> 06:31.074
Everything we do is built around making disciples.

06:31.235 --> 06:36.661
Our budget is built around making disciples who follow Jesus, love one another, and serve Los Angeles.

06:36.941 --> 06:41.866
Our staff is organized around making disciples who follow Jesus, love one another, and serve Los Angeles.

06:42.227 --> 06:48.914
We measure success by whether we are making disciples who follow Jesus, love one another, and serve Los Angeles.

06:49.314 --> 06:53.559
And then that plays out practically for us with our discipleship pathway.

06:54.400 --> 07:02.170
And beneath the categories of follow Jesus, love one another and serve Los Angeles, we have 12 dynamics of renewal.

07:02.250 --> 07:08.477
These are key areas of discipleship that we need to focus on, but also return to throughout our lives.

07:09.398 --> 07:15.826
And combined, they form a basic profile of the kind of disciples that we're aiming to be and to make.

07:16.386 --> 07:20.171
So to follow Jesus means you live by the story of Scripture.

07:20.452 --> 07:21.253
You know God.

07:21.453 --> 07:22.835
Your identity is in Christ.

07:23.156 --> 07:27.702
And you have formative practices that shape your heart and your character over time.

07:28.463 --> 07:30.426
But this isn't just about you as an individual.

07:30.626 --> 07:32.769
We are disciples who love one another.

07:33.350 --> 07:36.475
That means you learn to have healthy relationships.

07:36.495 --> 07:38.297
You experience healing from wounds.

07:38.337 --> 07:41.682
You're known in community and you belong to a church.

07:42.082 --> 07:44.205
And then together, we serve Los Angeles.

07:44.485 --> 07:46.548
That means you witness to Christ in word and deed.

07:47.088 --> 07:49.311
You do justice in a world of injustice.

07:49.391 --> 07:53.316
You work with God, learning to apply your faith to your vocation.

07:53.336 --> 07:58.002
And you make culture as image bearers of God who are in the world, but not of the world.

07:58.803 --> 08:05.090
So this is a profile of a disciple and a pathway for how we grow as disciples.

08:05.911 --> 08:11.218
And just to be clear, the discipleship pathway is not just another ministry in our church.

08:11.298 --> 08:18.007
It's the framework for all ministry in our church, and it flows directly from our mission to make disciples.

08:18.928 --> 08:23.114
And then lastly, in terms of who we are, we have 10 values as a church.

08:23.134 --> 08:30.284
And while I'm not gonna talk through every one of these, I will say that the secret sauce is in holding the tension in all of these values.

08:31.045 --> 08:36.192
And the phrase that captures that tension for us is orthodoxy in exile.

08:36.573 --> 08:40.498
So we are rooted in the city, but different from the city.

08:40.674 --> 08:43.477
We preach the word and we pursue justice.

08:43.658 --> 08:47.883
We're united in the gospel, but different in our cultural backgrounds.

08:48.283 --> 08:51.808
We follow Jesus alone, but learn to do so in all of life.

08:52.689 --> 08:57.014
And so at the end of the day, we're a church that believes that Jesus changes everything, amen?

08:58.295 --> 09:00.298
So that's who we are.

09:00.318 --> 09:03.762
That leads to the next question of where have we been?

09:04.898 --> 09:13.831
Well, today is an especially significant vision Sunday because this year we are celebrating our 20-year anniversary as a church.

09:14.312 --> 09:15.173
20 years!

09:15.193 --> 09:15.273
Wow!

09:18.618 --> 09:26.930
I mean, we started as a prayer meeting in a living room, and two decades later, we're a healthy and rooted church in the heart of Los Angeles.

09:27.458 --> 09:30.763
And we can't take this for granted one bit.

09:30.863 --> 09:37.652
I mean, it is a miracle of God's grace that we're still here, let alone healthy and thriving.

09:38.233 --> 09:42.018
And honestly, I've seen so many churches come and go in LA.

09:42.599 --> 09:47.626
I can think of several churches just in the last year that have closed down or moved out of the city.

09:47.646 --> 09:48.507
And I get it.

09:48.567 --> 09:52.012
It's a hard place to follow Jesus and to do church.

09:52.693 --> 09:56.338
But by God's grace, we're still here 20 years later.

09:57.026 --> 10:03.176
And in May, we're going to have a special celebration where we're going to reflect on what God has done over 20 years.

10:03.557 --> 10:09.306
We'll worship him for his faithfulness and then pray that he would do even greater things as we move forward.

10:09.987 --> 10:19.122
But today, I just want to quickly highlight the story of our church so that we can begin to celebrate God's faithfulness over the last two decades.

10:19.202 --> 10:28.574
It all started in 2006, when Pastor Tim Chatech led a small group of people with a simple vision of proclaiming the gospel in the heart of the city and seeing what God would do.

10:28.614 --> 10:33.821
The first service was held in the Michael Jackson Auditorium in Gardener Elementary.

10:34.521 --> 10:38.787
And the church was very small for the first year, but it grew.

10:38.807 --> 10:47.538
And going into 2007, we moved into Lacont Middle School, which is actually just right next door across the street here.

10:47.746 --> 10:57.737
And God was moving powerfully, and as we ran out of space in that middle school, this high school was being built on what was an old lot of an old TV studio.

10:58.637 --> 11:06.326
And once this high school was finished in the summer of 2008, before the students even came into the school, we started meeting here as a church.

11:07.947 --> 11:14.354
My family and I moved to Los Angeles and joined the church in 2013 at a time when the church had grown

11:14.466 --> 11:19.772
significantly, and we were really scrambling to build infrastructure and raise up leaders to keep up with the growth.

11:20.613 --> 11:31.045
And then two years later, in 2015, we sent our founding pastor, Tim Chatek, to plant reality London, and I stepped into the position for pastor for preaching and vision.

11:31.065 --> 11:42.578
And that wasn't a season, that season wasn't just a transition from Tim to me, it was a transition from us being a young church plant that was riding a lot of momentum,

11:42.658 --> 11:47.323
toward Lord willing becoming a healthy church that's making disciples from one generation to the next.

11:48.023 --> 11:50.305
And by God's grace, that's what's happened.

11:50.946 --> 12:04.759
And just as we were settling into that though, into that new identity as a church, we were then approached by another church, Hope International Bible Fellowship, right down the street here in East Hollywood.

12:05.400 --> 12:11.666
And long story short, their congregation joined our congregation and we inherited the Hope Center

12:11.746 --> 12:15.410
and off the office building as well as an incredible food ministry.

12:15.911 --> 12:18.874
And this was just a game changer for us as a church.

12:19.555 --> 12:25.262
But then again, just as we were settling into that new season, the pandemic hit in 2020.

12:26.544 --> 12:28.826
Remember doing everything on Zoom for that time?

12:28.886 --> 12:30.829
Brutal, brutal.

12:31.269 --> 12:34.553
Well, honestly, it was a hard season for us as a church.

12:35.254 --> 12:38.738
We had a lot of people in our church that moved out of the city.

12:39.042 --> 12:43.530
We had about 10 years of conversations about race and politics within one year.

12:43.570 --> 12:48.399
We couldn't meet in the school, so we were online for a full year.

12:48.419 --> 12:52.066
And then we met outside in a parking lot for several months.

12:52.146 --> 12:52.707
Remember that?

12:52.927 --> 12:54.069
Remember those good memories?

12:54.730 --> 12:55.752
Anyway, who was here for that?

12:55.792 --> 12:56.774
Who was in the parking lot?

12:56.814 --> 12:57.315
Look at that.

12:57.716 --> 12:58.758
We've come so far.

13:00.260 --> 13:03.346
But by God's grace, we weathered that storm.

13:03.586 --> 13:10.957
And the last three to four years have really been a season of reviving and rebuilding for us, building everything around our mission.

13:11.738 --> 13:14.482
And God has just been so gracious to us.

13:15.183 --> 13:19.289
I mean, so many of you have come to know Christ here or returned to Christ here.

13:19.349 --> 13:31.506
We've seen God knit lives together, friendships that feel like family, marriages that began in this community, meaningful work that was born here and children who are growing up amongst us.

13:32.066 --> 13:40.414
And I can't believe it's been 20 years, and I'm just so overwhelmed by how kind God has been to us.

13:41.955 --> 13:45.158
And that leads up to last year, 2025.

13:46.620 --> 13:50.523
And our vision in 2025 was to be on mission with Jesus.

13:51.184 --> 13:53.606
And man, did we have opportunities to do that.

13:54.567 --> 14:01.714
One year ago, from right now, a year ago, at this time, our city was literally on fire.

14:02.274 --> 14:12.305
and fires burned for over three weeks throughout the city with 18,000 homes and structures being destroyed and 180,000 people evacuating.

14:13.046 --> 14:16.891
It was one of the most devastating times in the history of our city.

14:17.672 --> 14:26.121
We had several people in our church who lost their homes, many who had to evacuate, and almost all of us had a bag packed not knowing what would happen.

14:27.022 --> 14:30.386
And yet, God looked on our city with compassion.

14:30.882 --> 14:32.984
He's the God who's with us in the fire.

14:33.505 --> 14:37.690
He's the God who enters into our suffering and he's the God of restoration.

14:37.730 --> 14:43.737
And by his grace, he invited us into his beautiful work of restoration in this city.

14:44.417 --> 14:51.245
People started donating money and more money, people from outside the church and outside the state and all kinds of people were donating money.

14:51.265 --> 14:56.171
And before we knew it, we had over $380,000 in our fire relief fund.

14:56.811 --> 14:59.154
And so we prayed and God gave us a vision

14:59.522 --> 15:06.511
to help people who have lost their homes, churches who've lost their buildings, and foster families that were impacted by the fires.

15:07.251 --> 15:10.295
And so we created three different committees of people in our church.

15:11.096 --> 15:17.884
And when the world moved on after the initial impact, these committees got to work and they distributed all of this money.

15:17.904 --> 15:22.590
$120,000 were given to three different churches in Los Angeles.

15:22.610 --> 15:25.714
$183,000.

15:25.794 --> 15:31.845
were distributed to 32 different families or individuals who lost their homes or who lost work because of the fires.

15:32.426 --> 15:38.316
And $69,000 was given to foster families or vulnerable families who were impacted by the fires.

15:39.097 --> 15:42.102
And church, that wasn't strategy.

15:42.142 --> 15:43.044
That was grace.

15:43.705 --> 15:45.148
That wasn't us being impressive.

15:45.348 --> 15:47.171
That was God being faithful.

15:47.532 --> 15:51.058
And we should give Him praise for all that He did in the midst of the amen.

15:56.226 --> 16:04.161
Now another massive event for us in 2025 was that we did our first ever capital campaign, which we called rebuilding for renewal.

16:05.102 --> 16:13.798
And as I mentioned earlier, we had been given two buildings and while they're beautiful, they're also deeply broken, not up to code, and barely even functional.

16:14.480 --> 16:20.210
And so in 2025, we set out to raise funds to steward these sacred spaces.

16:20.290 --> 16:30.083
And the goal is to raise enough money above and beyond our regular giving to make these buildings become a home for our church and a hub of renewal for our city for generations to come.

16:30.924 --> 16:40.758
And while we'll still continue to meet here on Sunday mornings, these buildings give us roots in the city of space for ministry throughout the week and a tangible way to serve our city.

16:41.499 --> 16:46.726
And so we laid out division, we shared the need and we ask you all to give sacrificially to the Lord's work.

16:47.367 --> 16:49.650
And by God's abundant grace,

16:49.890 --> 16:57.223
We exceeded our minimum goal, and the congregation pledged $6.2 million over the next two years.

16:57.363 --> 16:57.964
Praise God.

17:02.172 --> 17:10.326
Now, I told you all when we started the campaign was that one thing was I didn't want it to be weird, no thermometers or manipulation, okay?

17:10.366 --> 17:10.687
Check.

17:11.088 --> 17:12.370
I think we got through that.

17:12.514 --> 17:20.791
But second, I told you that my prayer is that God would use the capital campaign to do a work in our church far greater than just raising money.

17:21.433 --> 17:23.016
And that's exactly what he did.

17:23.036 --> 17:31.193
I mean, the way that he provided the money is incredible, but what's even better is how he's used this campaign to mature us as a church.

17:31.754 --> 17:33.618
We're more united around our vision.

17:33.794 --> 17:36.839
We've learned how to view money as a matter of discipleship.

17:36.859 --> 17:40.465
We're more informed about how our staff works and what Sir valet does.

17:40.525 --> 17:46.114
And most of all, we learned to pray and depend on God more than we have before.

17:47.136 --> 17:55.570
I'll never forget after our celebration Sunday where we announced the pledges that I was talking to someone in our church in the courtyard and he said,

17:55.778 --> 17:58.622
Man, I got to be honest, I never thought we would raise that much money.

17:58.802 --> 17:59.723
I never thought we would.

18:00.224 --> 18:04.310
And he said, once you announced it, he said, I was looking around the auditorium.

18:04.590 --> 18:07.154
He said, I see our church differently now.

18:07.795 --> 18:11.981
He said, it's easy to look around and see a crowd and think, it's LA.

18:12.281 --> 18:15.666
It's a bunch of noncommittal people who are kind of here for what they get out of it.

18:15.686 --> 18:18.149
And there's maybe a small core that's committed.

18:18.169 --> 18:21.714
And he said, I'm looking around saying, these people are really committed.

18:22.178 --> 18:27.626
These people are really united around what God has called us to do in this city.

18:27.646 --> 18:29.169
And I think that's exactly right.

18:29.970 --> 18:35.138
And that's because this renovation is all about being on mission with Jesus.

18:35.799 --> 18:43.370
We're not renovating our buildings to be an insular, more comfortable community, but in order to reach deeper and further into our city with the gospel.

18:44.512 --> 18:45.714
And yet all of this

18:45.826 --> 18:48.430
is because of the generosity of God.

18:48.450 --> 18:51.073
He has been so generous to us.

18:51.234 --> 18:52.956
And for all that, we should give him praise.

18:52.996 --> 18:57.422
So can we praise God as we look back on this year and sing what he's done?

18:57.462 --> 19:08.498
And so the fire relief and the capital campaign, those were two big headlines throughout 2025, but God did so much more, so much more.

19:08.610 --> 19:17.363
We spent all of 2025 in the book of Acts, learning how to be on mission with Jesus and how his mission advances through the church empowered by the spirit.

19:18.044 --> 19:27.898
And we're seeing how that happened in the Roman Empire in the book of Acts, and that we're seeing the same God do the same kinds of things right here in Los Angeles.

19:28.159 --> 19:35.730
In fact, at the beginning of the series, I told you that my hope was that in the first couple of weeks that you would have an increased burden for the lost.

19:36.066 --> 19:39.612
And then in the next couple of months that you would feel more equipped to reach the lost.

19:39.932 --> 19:44.920
And then by the end of the year that there'd be new believers sitting all around you.

19:44.940 --> 19:47.124
And that's exactly what's happened.

19:47.905 --> 19:55.678
I've heard the most amazing stories this year of people who were so far from Jesus, who are now following Jesus.

19:56.379 --> 20:03.410
And we've seen kids who are growing up in our church profess faith in Christ and live for Him on their own volition.

20:03.682 --> 20:09.150
So altogether, in 2025, we celebrated 42 baptisms.

20:09.190 --> 20:10.252
Can we praise God for that?

20:10.272 --> 20:11.694
42 baptisms.

20:13.236 --> 20:23.232
People from all walks of life, young and old, black, white, Hispanic, Asian, people who have come from church backgrounds, non-church backgrounds, all made new by Jesus.

20:24.113 --> 20:32.786
And what I love about almost every one of these conversion stories is that they involve one of you, somebody who is

20:32.898 --> 20:38.624
praying for them, sharing the gospel with them, inviting them to church and walking with them on their journey.

20:39.505 --> 20:44.109
And so, as we look back on 2025, there's so much more that I could talk about.

20:44.150 --> 20:50.616
I mean, like we did at another RFKC camp for 37 kids in the foster care system in L.A., amazing.

20:51.697 --> 21:00.306
We have 360 servant leaders who help make this place hospitable on Sundays and get an offering of worship to God.

21:00.418 --> 21:06.307
Servale served 72,000 meals last year out of the Hope Center.

21:06.547 --> 21:08.209
Absolutely incredible.

21:08.290 --> 21:11.474
In fact, that just reminds me of one quick story I wanna tell you.

21:14.198 --> 21:24.493
Servale earlier in 2025 was in a month where they're in a place of financial need and the church gives a large portion to Servale, but they also rely on outside fundraising as well.

21:25.074 --> 21:30.322
In one day, Kyle Miller, the executive director of Servale,

21:30.658 --> 21:33.502
We were meeting and we were just praying that God would provide.

21:33.582 --> 21:39.371
And we literally prayed like, God, just from somewhere, just provide God, we need your provision.

21:39.411 --> 21:52.210
And literally the next day, a former member of reality LA who moved out of the city and has become a very successful actor, got invited to be on celebrity wheel of fortune.

21:52.290 --> 21:58.058
And he went on Celebrity Wheel of Fortune and picked Servelle as his nonprofit that the proceeds would go to.

21:58.098 --> 22:03.145
And he crushed it and won $110,000 for Servelle.

22:03.205 --> 22:10.696
So God has been so good to us, providing in the most amazing ways.

22:10.836 --> 22:13.420
And 2025 was a full year.

22:13.921 --> 22:15.022
It was full of sorrow.

22:15.042 --> 22:16.104
It was full of joy.

22:16.144 --> 22:20.530
And yet in all of it, God was so gracious to us.

22:20.802 --> 22:26.190
And then looking back on last year gives us so much confidence as we look forward to this year.

22:26.310 --> 22:29.714
And so that leads to the next question, where are we going in 2026?

22:31.257 --> 22:33.880
Well, let's remember, we're not starting from scratch.

22:34.341 --> 22:37.225
In 2025, our vision was to be on mission with Jesus.

22:37.786 --> 22:44.835
And in this coming year, there are two things that we already feel deeply called to and committed to that's still aligned with that vision.

22:44.936 --> 22:47.119
So first is the book of Acts.

22:47.619 --> 22:49.522
We're just past the halfway book

22:49.602 --> 22:51.344
halfway point in the book of Acts.

22:51.905 --> 22:59.374
And the second half is where Paul goes into all these pagan cities, plants churches, and teaches them how to be faithful to Christ there.

22:59.874 --> 23:04.620
So it's definitely a blueprint for us in terms of being on mission in Los Angeles.

23:05.561 --> 23:12.690
And the second thing we're already committed to is the renovation, which is about being on mission in this city in a holistic way for a long time.

23:13.186 --> 23:19.513
So in 2026, we basically wanna double down on our vision of being on mission with Jesus.

23:20.214 --> 23:22.356
And I think this is more relevant than ever.

23:22.396 --> 23:27.302
People are so open, they're hungry, they're spiritually curious right now.

23:28.163 --> 23:32.328
What I see in our city is a disillusionment with the things of the world.

23:32.788 --> 23:38.034
People know, they're starting to learn at least that they can't find their hope in politics.

23:38.370 --> 23:41.234
They know that their hope can't be in artificial intelligence.

23:41.274 --> 23:43.597
They know that their hope is not in digital technology.

23:43.998 --> 23:47.182
And we're people who can say, there's hope in Christ.

23:47.643 --> 23:48.804
There's meaning in Christ.

23:48.824 --> 23:49.886
There's purpose in Christ.

23:49.906 --> 23:51.227
There's community in Christ.

23:51.247 --> 23:52.770
This is what people are longing for.

23:52.790 --> 24:02.002
And I'm having conversations with people regularly who don't have any other space to talk about spiritual questions.

24:02.178 --> 24:03.360
And so they're coming to church.

24:03.840 --> 24:07.786
I mean, I love that I'm meeting unbelievers every week who show up to our church.

24:07.826 --> 24:08.687
They Googled us.

24:09.148 --> 24:11.671
They Googled church in Los Angeles.

24:11.691 --> 24:12.993
They found us on social media.

24:13.294 --> 24:18.060
ChatGPT is telling people to come to reality LA, seriously.

24:18.080 --> 24:27.153
But most of all, you all are inviting your friends, your neighbors, your coworkers, and lives are being changed.

24:27.654 --> 24:30.578
I mean, I've seen just in the last few weeks,

24:30.850 --> 24:37.602
People who I thought would never become Christians, who are now following Jesus and telling others about him.

24:38.523 --> 24:42.851
And so I really think that there's a mission opportunity in our city right now.

24:42.911 --> 24:47.799
People are hungry, Jesus is on the move, and we wanna join him in what he's doing.

24:49.102 --> 24:56.274
And so while we wanna double down on last year's vision of being on mission with Jesus, we also wanna add a slight emphasis to this.

24:56.578 --> 25:03.026
Because being on mission isn't just a vision for a handful of people who are extroverts and passionate about evangelism.

25:03.767 --> 25:09.654
So in this year to come, our vision is for everyone to be on mission with Jesus.

25:10.195 --> 25:16.302
The whole church is called to participate in Christ's work in this city.

25:17.163 --> 25:20.648
And I wanna share an analogy with you that will help you understand this.

25:20.728 --> 25:25.874
I've shared it before, but hopefully this will just tattoo it on your brain, okay?

25:25.986 --> 25:31.034
A lot of people think of the church like a cruise ship.

25:31.054 --> 25:33.898
And on a cruise ship, you have two groups of people.

25:34.319 --> 25:38.585
There is a small group of people that do all the work, okay?

25:38.625 --> 25:43.753
These are the staff that makes the food and serve the food and changes your sheets and does the shows.

25:44.173 --> 25:50.002
There's a small group that does all the work and then there's a large group that's literally along for the ride, right?

25:50.114 --> 25:56.961
They do the chocolate fondue and sit by the pool and go to the shows and critique the paid professionals.

25:57.741 --> 26:18.642
Well, for the church, a lot of people think of the church like a cruise ship, that there's a small group of people, the people who are like fanatical about their faith or maybe it's like the leaders in the church, they do most of the work and everyone else is just kind of along the ride to show up when you can, critique the paid professionals from time to time.

26:18.850 --> 26:24.277
But what I want you to learn is that the church is not like a cruise ship, it's like a battleship.

26:24.918 --> 26:29.504
See, on a battleship, there's not two groups of people, a small group that do the work and one that are along for the ride.

26:29.885 --> 26:36.133
No, on a battleship, everyone has a role because everyone is in a mission together.

26:36.153 --> 26:42.642
And so we need to be like people on a battleship because we are in a spiritual war

26:42.850 --> 26:48.817
And we have been given a mission by God in this city, and everyone has a role to play.

26:49.057 --> 26:53.462
There's no coming along, just to be along for the ride.

26:54.063 --> 26:57.087
Everyone must be involved in the mission.

26:57.147 --> 27:05.196
And so I wanna speak to everyone in this room, because the mission of Jesus isn't for a few people, it's for all of us.

27:05.717 --> 27:10.322
No one gets a pass, no one is disqualified, and no one is meant to sit this out.

27:10.946 --> 27:12.970
And some of you are on the sidelines.

27:13.551 --> 27:18.060
You've been watching, observing, evaluating, but not participating.

27:18.681 --> 27:23.210
You've treated the church like an event you attend rather than a movement that you belong to.

27:23.230 --> 27:27.579
And listen, Jesus didn't save you for you to be a spectator.

27:27.599 --> 27:29.383
He calls you into the mission.

27:30.044 --> 27:31.647
So what's holding you back?

27:31.887 --> 27:33.170
I just want to plead with you.

27:33.602 --> 27:35.465
I mean, some of you, you're wounded.

27:35.605 --> 27:38.750
You've been hurt by life, maybe even by people in the church.

27:38.831 --> 27:46.603
My prayer is that you would experience healing and that you wouldn't stay isolated, but that you would step into this mission with humility and hope.

27:47.264 --> 27:48.767
Some of you are hard-hearted.

27:49.047 --> 27:53.014
You've grown guarded and cynical and jaded.

27:53.134 --> 27:58.162
And my prayer is that the love of God would soften your heart and draw you into his mission.

27:58.530 --> 28:04.456
Some of you are apathetic, you're not opposed, you're just numb, you're not hostile, you're just disengaged.

28:05.096 --> 28:13.244
My prayer is that God would awaken in you a holy urgency so that you'd remember what you're saved from and what you're saved for.

28:14.225 --> 28:16.307
Some of you straight up are living double lives.

28:16.647 --> 28:23.433
You declare Jesus as Lord and live that out on Sundays and then you're a completely different person around other people in your lives.

28:24.154 --> 28:28.338
Jesus doesn't shame you, but he calls you to repentance, full surrender,

28:28.578 --> 28:31.062
and to participate in His work.

28:31.082 --> 28:32.605
Some of you are just discouraged.

28:32.685 --> 28:37.032
You've tried, you've prayed, you've stepped out, and you're tired.

28:37.593 --> 28:39.917
But I want to say to you, take heart.

28:40.478 --> 28:42.261
The mission doesn't depend on your strength.

28:42.442 --> 28:44.565
It's carried by the power of the Spirit.

28:45.487 --> 28:48.452
And so wherever you find yourself today, hear this clearly.

28:49.273 --> 28:54.482
Jesus is calling you, not someday, not after you get your life together, but today.

28:54.818 --> 28:58.366
We need everyone on mission with Jesus.

28:58.767 --> 29:01.332
That's what we're after in 2026.

29:02.956 --> 29:04.359
And this isn't just an idea.

29:04.419 --> 29:06.143
It's a command from God's word.

29:06.684 --> 29:10.232
And so now I want to show you how this vision is grounded in Scripture.

29:10.452 --> 29:11.154
All right.

29:11.234 --> 29:14.600
We've spent the better part, or we're spending the better part of two years in the book of Acts.

29:15.241 --> 29:21.773
But today I wanna look to the Old Testament story of Jonah, which in a lot of ways is a precursor to the mission of the church and the New Testament.

29:22.314 --> 29:28.465
And so if you have your Bible, you can open it up to Jonah chapter three, or I'll have the words on the screen behind me.

29:29.366 --> 29:35.858
But while some of you are turning there, let me just give you some context of the story of leading up to Jonah chapter three.

29:36.130 --> 29:44.080
So what's going on is that Nineveh is the city in the ancient world, the capital of Assyria, and it was known for its cruelty and oppression.

29:44.721 --> 29:48.126
But God sends Jonah to that city.

29:48.186 --> 29:52.531
He says, arise and go to Nineveh, that great city and preach to them.

29:53.172 --> 29:54.854
But Jonah doesn't want any part of it.

29:55.335 --> 29:57.638
Nineveh's evil, they're wicked, they're cruel.

29:58.078 --> 30:03.986
Jonah resists, he runs away from God fleeing to another city on a ship on the sea.

30:04.674 --> 30:06.978
And as he's on this ship, a storm comes.

30:07.198 --> 30:14.990
And everyone on this ship begins to cry out to all their different gods, but Jonah realizes in the midst of the storm that it's because of him.

30:15.050 --> 30:17.454
So he tells them, throw me over.

30:17.494 --> 30:18.235
And they do.

30:18.315 --> 30:21.079
They throw him over the sea calms.

30:21.540 --> 30:25.626
And it says, the Lord appoints a great fish to swallow up Jonah.

30:26.467 --> 30:29.212
He's in the belly of the fish for three days and three nights.

30:29.232 --> 30:29.953
And what is he doing there?

30:29.993 --> 30:30.834
He's praying.

30:31.618 --> 30:36.944
And then the Lord commands the fish and it spits Jonah up out onto the dry land.

30:37.485 --> 30:40.228
And that's where we pick up in Jonah chapter three.

30:40.948 --> 30:50.239
Jonah has resisted the mission of God, but what we're going to see is God's relentless mission to the city and his patience with his reluctant people.

30:51.060 --> 30:52.461
So look at Jonah chapter three with me.

30:53.823 --> 31:00.210
Then the word of the Lord came to Jonah the second time saying, arise, go to Nineveh, that great city.

31:00.418 --> 31:02.882
and call out against it the message that I tell you.

31:03.763 --> 31:06.767
So Jonah arose and went to Nineveh according to the word of the Lord.

31:07.548 --> 31:11.173
Now Nineveh was an exceedingly great city, three days journey in breath.

31:12.015 --> 31:18.384
Jonah began to go into the city, going a days journey, and he called out, yet 40 days, and Nineveh shall be overthrown.

31:18.444 --> 31:21.929
And the people of Nineveh believed God.

31:22.610 --> 31:28.498
They called for a fast and put on sackcloth from the greatest of them to the least of them.

31:29.506 --> 31:40.977
Wow, so let me walk through what's happening here, because this short passage tells us exactly what we need to know about God's mission, our role in the transformation of a city.

31:41.418 --> 31:45.301
So first, we see God's mission, and that God's mission is to the city.

31:45.682 --> 31:49.185
In verse two, he says, arise, go to Nineveh, that great city.

31:49.886 --> 31:53.189
Now we have to be clear about what great means here.

31:53.389 --> 31:55.231
Nineveh was not morally great.

31:55.571 --> 31:58.354
It was violent, oppressive, and notorious for its evil.

31:58.882 --> 32:04.487
But great here means that this city is large, influential, and full of people made in the image of God.

32:05.328 --> 32:11.794
God looks at a city, and Jonah wants to avoid it, but God says go to that great city.

32:12.995 --> 32:17.540
And because God's heart, he does this because God's heart has always been for cities.

32:18.200 --> 32:23.725
Cities like Nineveh, Rome, Athens, even cities like Los Angeles.

32:24.887 --> 32:28.530
But why is God on mission to the city when it's so full of evil?

32:29.186 --> 32:33.992
Well, because as we see in this passage, God's mission is driven by compassion.

32:34.813 --> 32:53.778
Actually, in Jonah chapter four, the last verse in chapter four, verse 11, the Lord says this, should I not have compassion on Nineveh, that great city in which there are more than 120,000 persons who do not know their right hand from their left and also much the cattle?

32:54.242 --> 33:01.452
So God sees people who are lost, and he sees them like sheep without a shepherd, and his heart is moved toward them.

33:02.273 --> 33:10.384
So God's mission is driven by compassion, but then we also learn that God's mission is persistent in the face of opposition.

33:10.945 --> 33:16.032
So notice in verse one, it says, the word of the Lord came to Jonah the second time.

33:17.033 --> 33:18.054
Jonah had already ran.

33:18.095 --> 33:19.617
He already disobeyed.

33:19.657 --> 33:23.602
He already failed, and yet God comes again.

33:24.226 --> 33:29.854
This is the mission of God who is persistent with his mission and patient with his people.

33:31.216 --> 33:39.768
And even though Jonah had ran from God, God doesn't replace Jonah, he restores him and he invites him into his mission again.

33:39.808 --> 33:46.298
And so we've seen God's mission, but now let's focus on what we learn about our role.

33:47.079 --> 33:51.986
Well, Jonah was sent on a mission and so are we.

33:52.450 --> 33:55.814
It's not our mission, it's God's, but He's called us into it.

33:56.615 --> 34:01.981
And what's clear is that Jonah's role is not to save or convert people, only God can do that.

34:02.822 --> 34:05.785
Jonah is simply called to tell people about God.

34:06.686 --> 34:09.710
And Jonah's message is strikingly short.

34:10.250 --> 34:13.654
In the original language of Hebrew, it's literally five words.

34:14.615 --> 34:20.402
There's no persuasion, no strategy, no technique, just obedience and a message from God.

34:21.826 --> 34:22.467
And here's the key.

34:22.928 --> 34:24.510
The power is not in the messenger.

34:24.550 --> 34:27.475
The power is in the message that God sends.

34:28.456 --> 34:30.299
And that's so freeing, isn't it?

34:31.060 --> 34:33.204
God doesn't need impressive people.

34:33.284 --> 34:35.447
He works through obedient people.

34:35.968 --> 34:40.896
And that's what he's asking of us to play a role in his mission.

34:42.478 --> 34:50.130
You know, one of our deacons sent me an Instagram reel a little while ago from this account called Subway Takes.

34:50.498 --> 34:52.401
And it's a fun account.

34:52.802 --> 34:57.609
This guy basically sits on the subway in New York and asks people for their take on something.

34:57.990 --> 35:00.033
And so people give all kinds of takes, right?

35:00.113 --> 35:03.218
One person's take is that the government controls the weather.

35:04.280 --> 35:07.305
Another person's take is that dogs should have to wear shoes.

35:08.026 --> 35:09.629
It's pretty convincing if you listen to it.

35:10.630 --> 35:17.842
But there's one person, this woman, she's wearing oversized sunglasses and tattoos all over her arms and her take.

35:18.210 --> 35:21.478
is that religious people don't actually believe what they say.

35:22.481 --> 35:24.486
And he says, 100% disagree.

35:24.606 --> 35:27.774
And then she starts to defend herself.

35:27.794 --> 35:29.057
And she explains why.

35:29.077 --> 35:34.510
And she says, because if they really believed it, they would tell everyone else about it nonstop.

35:35.252 --> 35:35.954
And she says,

35:36.034 --> 35:40.999
She literally says, I quit eating sugar and I can't stop telling everyone about it.

35:41.299 --> 35:48.226
Like, how could these people believe that they'll go to hell apart from God or have eternal life with them and they don't talk to anyone about it?

35:48.867 --> 35:59.377
I mean, she says that she thinks most religious people are liars and hypocrites because they say they believe this stuff but they don't care whether it actually impacts anyone else.

36:00.498 --> 36:04.242
And it's a fascinating video but it's convicting.

36:04.770 --> 36:08.616
I mean, if we had the cure for cancer, we'd be telling everyone about it.

36:09.377 --> 36:14.285
But we have something even better, the remedy for sin and the source of eternal life.

36:15.027 --> 36:18.793
How can we not let as many people possible know about it?

36:19.594 --> 36:31.954
And that's what God is calling us into, to play a key role in his mission of being heralds of the gospel, proclaiming the good news to people who genuinely don't know.

36:33.090 --> 36:35.673
And so we've seen God's mission in our role.

36:36.835 --> 36:39.518
But Jonah chapter three answers one central question.

36:40.119 --> 36:45.085
What does it look like when God sends ordinary, reluctant people on his mission?

36:45.766 --> 36:50.852
Look at verse five, it says, in the people of Nineveh believed God.

36:51.893 --> 36:56.138
So they didn't believe Jonah, they believed God.

36:56.939 --> 37:02.226
From the greatest to the least, and we actually learned in the verses following this, that even the cattle

37:02.402 --> 37:05.205
put on sackcloth and ashes as a sign of repentance.

37:05.606 --> 37:08.389
The whole city is impacted by the message.

37:09.190 --> 37:12.234
And this is what God does when his word goes forth.

37:12.995 --> 37:14.096
It happened in Nineveh.

37:14.377 --> 37:16.479
It can happen right here in Los Angeles.

37:17.881 --> 37:20.464
But Jonah three doesn't just show us a model for mission.

37:20.985 --> 37:23.808
It ultimately points us to the savior of the world.

37:24.609 --> 37:27.393
Jesus is the true and better Jonah.

37:27.893 --> 37:28.434
Think about it.

37:28.866 --> 37:31.449
Jonah was sent to a great city that he didn't want to save.

37:32.029 --> 37:34.572
Jesus was sent to a broken world he deeply loved.

37:35.253 --> 37:36.775
Jonah went reluctantly.

37:37.115 --> 37:38.396
Jesus came willingly.

37:39.037 --> 37:41.320
Jonah preached judgment from outside the city.

37:41.680 --> 37:46.265
Jesus entered into the city and to our suffering and he bore the judgment himself.

37:47.066 --> 37:49.268
Jonah announced destruction in 40 days.

37:49.789 --> 37:54.514
Jesus absorbed destruction on the cross so that mercy could flow forever.

37:55.330 --> 37:58.738
And did you know that Jesus actually talked about the story of Jonah?

37:59.379 --> 38:09.803
In the New Testament, Jesus says, just as Jonah was in the belly of the fish for three days and three nights, so the son of man would be in the depths of the earth and then rise again.

38:09.823 --> 38:14.674
And this is the apex of the entire story of Scripture.

38:15.298 --> 38:24.408
that Jesus, who is the eternal Son of God, became a man so that he could die on the cross for our sins and rise from the grave so that we could have eternal life.

38:24.669 --> 38:28.493
And then ascend to the right hand of the Father to reign over the world as king.

38:28.533 --> 38:32.117
And that brings us to the Book of Acts.

38:33.158 --> 38:37.063
And after Jesus rises from the grave, he doesn't say mission accomplished.

38:37.143 --> 38:41.768
He says, as the Father has sent me, so I send you.

38:41.828 --> 38:43.570
That's the Book of Acts.

38:44.034 --> 38:49.743
The mission of Jesus continuing through ordinary people in the church who are empowered by the spirit.

38:50.404 --> 38:57.014
Not perfect people, not fearless people, but forgiven, spirit-filled, sent people.

38:58.496 --> 39:02.241
In Jonah 3, God sends one reluctant prophet to one great city.

39:03.103 --> 39:06.828
In Acts, the risen Jesus sends his church to the nations.

39:07.670 --> 39:09.152
And now, here we are.

39:09.172 --> 39:13.298
The same God, the same gospel, the same mission,

39:13.634 --> 39:15.077
in a great city once again.

39:15.117 --> 39:18.764
And that's why this isn't just a story to admire.

39:19.065 --> 39:20.829
It's a movement to join.

39:21.330 --> 39:24.676
We need everyone on mission with Jesus.

39:24.757 --> 39:25.077
Amen?

39:25.097 --> 39:26.220
Amen.

39:27.242 --> 39:31.410
All right, so that's our vision, grounded in scripture.

39:32.098 --> 39:36.303
But now I wanna get more practical and talk about three goals that we have as a church in 2026.

39:37.464 --> 39:40.808
These are three practical ways of getting everyone on mission with Jesus, okay?

39:40.868 --> 39:43.531
And the first is to engage the essentials.

39:43.651 --> 39:49.557
Now, I need to set this up by explaining a problem that has emerged in our church.

39:49.577 --> 39:58.728
So out of a desire to have a robust approach to discipleship and to show Jesus' impact on all of life, we've developed a lot of ministries.

39:58.748 --> 40:00.850
There's a lot going on, and that's great.

40:01.570 --> 40:06.919
But we haven't always clarified where to start, how to prioritize, and what to do next.

40:07.580 --> 40:18.860
And so sometimes, I think it's felt like there's a ministry buffet with lots going on, and people either get confused because they're not sure what to do, or they feel guilty because they're not doing it all.

40:19.641 --> 40:24.570
And so, if you've felt that way as a leader, I wanna apologize to you, okay?

40:25.211 --> 40:26.834
That's not on you.

40:27.010 --> 40:28.392
That's on us as leaders.

40:28.572 --> 40:33.658
We're doing the best that we can, but it's clear that we have some shortcomings and I think this is one of them.

40:34.118 --> 40:42.788
So here's what we're going to do to remedy this and to create more clarity moving forward as a church, right?

40:42.808 --> 40:47.654
There are four things that we expect every person in the church to do, okay?

40:48.134 --> 40:53.120
Four essentials for being involved in the church in a healthy way as disciples.

40:53.580 --> 40:54.962
And then everything else,

40:55.266 --> 40:57.229
is recommended for deeper discipleship.

40:57.990 --> 41:01.616
All right, so four essentials and they're built around our vision and our mission.

41:01.776 --> 41:07.625
So the first essential is to gather on Sundays because everything flows from the gospel.

41:08.286 --> 41:16.298
So according to scripture, it's not that we all have our private individual spirituality and then we tack on a church service every once in a while.

41:16.899 --> 41:24.210
No, the gathering of the church is to retell the story of the gospel and it's the fountainhead of everything that we do throughout the week.

41:25.250 --> 41:45.073
But the problem is, even though Sunday gatherings are so important in the life of the church, is that recent trends show that the average regular church goer only attends church twice a month, which means that they're probably just doing it when it's convenient, when they feel like it, when their friends are going, or when nothing else is going on.

41:45.874 --> 41:47.316
And this is a major problem.

41:47.576 --> 41:52.402
Hebrews 10 tells us, do not give up meeting together as some are in the habit of doing.

41:53.026 --> 41:57.894
And Sundays are not the whole of the Christian life, but they are a very important part of it.

41:58.475 --> 42:01.781
So the first essential is to gather on Sundays.

42:02.502 --> 42:07.811
The second is to engage the discipleship pathway to learn to follow Jesus.

42:08.392 --> 42:16.946
Now I've already unpacked our discipleship pathway, and we've been trying to get people to go through this over the last couple of years through an online tool.

42:17.218 --> 42:25.391
But we've recognized over the last couple of years just the importance of being together with people in person and the need to be guided through this by leaders.

42:26.072 --> 42:30.659
So this year, we're going to massively prioritize this and shift things up.

42:31.200 --> 42:38.371
And we're gonna offer 10-week discipleship cohorts on Sundays right after church, 12 to 130.

42:38.571 --> 42:43.218
Like, come to church, you're already here, you can go take part in a discipleship cohort

42:43.330 --> 42:47.516
And what we'll do in these 10 weeks is go through the 12 dynamics of renewal.

42:47.596 --> 42:54.485
So every week we'll have a short Bible teaching on that dynamic and then we'll break up into smaller cohorts where we'll do discipleship together.

42:55.126 --> 42:57.509
And then we're gonna do this three times throughout the year.

42:57.549 --> 43:02.596
And the goal is to get as many people as possible to go through the discipleship pathway.

43:03.518 --> 43:06.542
We're encouraging people to commit to the whole 10 weeks in a row.

43:06.582 --> 43:12.530
But if you need to, you can sign up for three or four weeks at a time and then piece those together throughout the year.

43:12.706 --> 43:15.730
And I know that a lot of you have already gone through this online.

43:15.850 --> 43:16.351
That's great.

43:16.751 --> 43:20.156
If you want, we'd love to have you be a leader for one of these cohorts.

43:20.756 --> 43:23.160
And then for everyone, you can sign up for this today.

43:23.240 --> 43:27.105
We're maxing, our capacity for this is 125 people.

43:27.525 --> 43:29.428
My hope is that we max it out today.

43:29.668 --> 43:32.191
We want to get, and other people got to wait for the next one.

43:32.452 --> 43:35.936
We want to get as many people possible through the discipleship cohorts.

43:36.517 --> 43:37.458
So that's the,

43:37.890 --> 43:42.117
Second essential, the third is to be involved in Christian community.

43:42.137 --> 43:43.259
This is how we love one another.

43:44.421 --> 43:49.089
And you know this, we're not called to follow Jesus alone, but to do so together.

43:49.109 --> 43:56.361
I think about a gentleman in our church, he's new to our church, and I bumped into him in the Hope Center last year.

43:56.401 --> 43:59.286
And he said, I'm going to my first community group tonight.

43:59.586 --> 44:01.169
And I said, amazing, that's awesome.

44:01.209 --> 44:02.151
I'm so excited for you.

44:02.171 --> 44:04.114
And he goes, no, you don't understand.

44:04.514 --> 44:09.942
I became a Christian 40 years ago and I've never really had Christian community.

44:10.663 --> 44:15.269
And then I said, wow, I'm really happy that you are going to community group tonight.

44:16.110 --> 44:20.837
And so then I saw on the next Sunday and I asked him, I said, how was it?

44:20.897 --> 44:21.478
How did it go?

44:21.498 --> 44:23.241
And he said, life changing.

44:23.601 --> 44:28.067
So I didn't realize how much I needed this and I can't believe I've been going without it.

44:28.087 --> 44:29.750
This group is like family.

44:30.471 --> 44:32.754
And that's the way that it's meant to be.

44:33.218 --> 44:34.981
And so we need community.

44:35.261 --> 44:40.850
And for us as a church, we offer community groups as a formal way to be involved in community.

44:41.351 --> 44:44.796
And we build a lot of our care structure with our elders and deacons around that.

44:45.377 --> 44:50.845
But being in a reality LA community group isn't the only way of having Christian community in your life.

44:51.586 --> 44:56.594
I think that's ideal because you have a shared commitment to a broader community and mission.

44:56.834 --> 45:04.122
But the key is just that you have Christians in your life that you regularly get together with explicitly for the purpose of Christian fellowship.

45:04.743 --> 45:10.649
Sharing life, you're meeting each other's needs, you're praying together, you're speaking the truth of the gospel into each other's lives.

45:11.370 --> 45:14.233
So that's the third essential, be involved in Christian community.

45:14.574 --> 45:17.417
And then fourth, serve in some capacity, okay?

45:18.538 --> 45:22.162
I mean, Jesus says the Son of Man did not come to be served but to serve.

45:22.306 --> 45:27.594
And so as disciples of Jesus, our posture towards one another in the city is a posture of service.

45:28.375 --> 45:30.999
And there are all kinds of ways that you can serve in the church.

45:31.039 --> 45:35.506
You can serve on Sundays with set up or tear down or kidsmen or hospitality.

45:35.546 --> 45:40.473
You can serve throughout the week at the Hope Center with Serve LA or one of our mission partners in the city.

45:40.513 --> 45:46.322
You can serve as a community group leader or in particular ministries like Gospel care or vocational groups.

45:46.754 --> 45:52.342
But once again, I want to clarify that serving in a formal role in the church isn't the only way to serve.

45:52.482 --> 45:57.008
We're not saying being involved in Christian programs or ministries equals maturity.

45:57.729 --> 46:05.240
I just want you to have a level of intentionality with service so that if somebody asks you where do you serve, then you'd be able to answer that question.

46:06.041 --> 46:07.283
So let me quickly review.

46:07.303 --> 46:08.865
There's four essentials.

46:09.626 --> 46:10.587
Gather on Sundays.

46:11.549 --> 46:13.151
Engage the discipleship pathway.

46:13.692 --> 46:15.474
Be involved in Christian community.

46:15.746 --> 46:17.849
and serve in some capacity.

46:18.410 --> 46:21.695
And then everything else is recommended for deeper discipleship.

46:22.316 --> 46:23.638
And we do a lot of different things.

46:23.658 --> 46:25.320
We offer a lot of different ministries.

46:25.460 --> 46:27.283
And I hope that lots of people do those.

46:27.944 --> 46:35.095
But honestly, if you're not doing these four essentials, that's where we'd want you to first focus your time and your energy.

46:36.377 --> 46:40.082
In fact, what I want to do right now is I want you to assess

46:40.354 --> 46:43.017
where you're at on these four essentials.

46:43.177 --> 46:45.920
So there's gonna be a QR code on the screen behind me.

46:46.400 --> 46:50.024
I want you to go ahead and pull out your phone and go to that, all right?

46:51.566 --> 46:55.910
Go to this site and this is going to be a self-assessment for you.

46:55.990 --> 46:57.632
So as I'm talking, just go for it.

46:57.652 --> 46:59.534
I'll try and get out of the way in a second.

47:00.355 --> 47:07.122
But go ahead and pull this up and I want you to assess yourself, how many of these four essentials are you doing?

47:07.778 --> 47:11.823
Maybe there were blind spots in your life or key areas that you've underestimated.

47:11.863 --> 47:15.388
And so we want everyone to do this anonymous survey.

47:15.408 --> 47:16.690
It's anonymous, okay?

47:17.431 --> 47:18.792
Should take you about 30 seconds.

47:19.674 --> 47:21.576
And we want to do this for two reasons.

47:21.916 --> 47:30.728
All right, one is for you to reflect on your own life and to think about, okay, where am I imbalanced?

47:30.768 --> 47:31.890
Am I missing something?

47:31.910 --> 47:33.512
Do I have blind spots?

47:33.572 --> 47:35.314
We want you to reflect on your own life.

47:35.810 --> 47:45.162
And then second, this will help our leadership to see where the needs are in our church so that we can better equip you all to be involved in a healthy and holistic way.

47:46.083 --> 48:04.466
So take a second, get there, go through that survey as quick as you can, and I'll just remind you as you're doing that, these four essentials to gather on Sundays, to engage our discipleship pathway,

48:05.186 --> 48:10.295
to be involved in Christian community and to serve in some capacity, okay?

48:11.397 --> 48:12.739
Do that as quickly as you can now.

48:12.759 --> 48:20.773
We also have, we'll have that QR code in the courtyard on some material that you can do if it's not working for you here for whatever reasons.

48:21.133 --> 48:26.122
But we would love for you to be able to do that and more importantly, to reflect on your own life.

48:26.663 --> 48:30.770
And then hopefully at the end of the year, you can look back at this and realize, I've grown.

48:31.074 --> 48:32.055
I've grown in this area.

48:32.075 --> 48:36.582
I'm involved in the church in a really healthy way as a disciple of Jesus.

48:38.245 --> 48:42.511
All right, so that's our first goal is to engage the essentials.

48:42.611 --> 48:46.757
We want as many people as possible just to engage in that most basic way.

48:47.238 --> 48:50.483
All right, the second goal is to rebuild for renewal.

48:51.264 --> 48:53.627
This will be really important for our church in 2026.

48:54.368 --> 48:56.151
And here's where we have the pledges.

48:56.191 --> 48:58.194
We did our capital campaign last year.

48:58.214 --> 49:00.818
We need to continue to fulfill those pledges, of course.

49:01.090 --> 49:03.113
But here's where we're at in the process now.

49:04.355 --> 49:14.569
Over the last several months, we finalized the plans for the renovation and now we're going through the permitting process with the city and we're waiting to hear back from contractors on exact prices.

49:14.629 --> 49:16.031
That should actually happen really soon.

49:17.192 --> 49:24.242
The plan is to begin construction in July or August and then that should take about a year to do the construction.

49:24.674 --> 49:33.985
And then in March, we're going to do a little refresher on the vision for the campaign, and we'll give an opportunity for new people in the church to join in on that.

49:34.166 --> 49:43.377
So if you're new to our church in the last year, you might be hearing some of this and not fully sure what we're talking about, we'll kind of reopen that for new people in the church and then move forward there.

49:43.397 --> 49:49.304
If anything, that will keep us all informed, especially so we know how to pray throughout this process.

49:49.985 --> 49:51.927
So that's our second goal is to rebuild for renewal.

49:51.967 --> 49:54.290
And then the third is to share the gospel.

49:54.690 --> 50:04.949
I mean, we want to be on mission with Jesus, and mission is broader than just sharing the gospel, but we want to specifically focus on proclaiming the good news of Jesus.

50:05.510 --> 50:10.700
We want to see lots of people become Christians this year, and that happens through hearing the gospel.

50:11.662 --> 50:18.194
A woman in our church told me a story recently that she had surgery done on her eyes.

50:18.370 --> 50:20.853
and they didn't put her under for the surgery.

50:21.334 --> 50:31.228
So she's having surgery done on her eyes and the doctor is having conversation with her throughout the whole thing the entire time while he's operating on her eyes.

50:31.849 --> 50:41.402
And so they get to talking, he hears that she's a Christian and really interested curious to start asking her all these questions about Christianity while he's operating on her eyes.

50:42.063 --> 50:47.250
And finally he says, so what's your elevator pitch for Christianity?

50:47.970 --> 50:52.016
Like, can you imagine in the operating room, like, what's your elevator pitch for Christianity?

50:52.257 --> 50:53.058
Here's the beautiful thing.

50:53.398 --> 50:54.200
She was ready.

50:54.220 --> 51:04.796
And what she did was laid out the gospel, right, right there, laying on her back, you know, who knows what's going on with her eyes, which is lays out the gospel for this doctor to hear.

51:04.836 --> 51:11.666
And what I love about that is that people are hungry, they're curious, conversations are happening in unexpected places.

51:11.987 --> 51:13.970
The question is, are you ready?

51:14.722 --> 51:17.606
When somebody asks you, what's your elevator pitch for Christianity?

51:17.666 --> 51:18.187
Are you ready?

51:18.788 --> 51:20.290
When somebody says, why do you go to church?

51:20.931 --> 51:23.735
When somebody says, wait, you're a Christian, what's the deal with that?

51:24.255 --> 51:25.237
Are you ready?

51:25.657 --> 51:27.319
And there's a lot of ways to be able to go about that.

51:27.340 --> 51:31.285
You can tell the story of scripture, you can share your testimony of what God's done in your life.

51:31.305 --> 51:40.658
You can have a scripture that you know that you'll go to in that scenario, but I want you to be ready and I want us to be expectant that when we proclaim the gospel,

51:40.930 --> 51:43.553
that people are going to hear and be transformed.

51:43.874 --> 51:46.217
So we want to be ready to share the gospel.

51:46.798 --> 51:48.840
Acts is going to continue to equip us for that.

51:49.221 --> 51:52.845
We'll have an evangelism workshop that's going to give us really practical tools for that.

51:53.306 --> 52:03.339
We're going to do several more Q and A's after Sunday gatherings throughout the year to make sure that we're creating space where skeptics know that they are welcome and questions are encouraged.

52:03.720 --> 52:05.522
So that's where we're going.

52:05.542 --> 52:08.626
2026, here's kind of a recap of that, our vision.

52:08.866 --> 52:11.449
is for everyone to be on mission with Jesus.

52:12.350 --> 52:16.574
And then as we're on mission with Jesus, we have three focus areas, goals that we've set.

52:16.594 --> 52:21.820
We wanna engage the essentials, rebuild for renewal, and share the gospel.

52:22.340 --> 52:23.822
That's where we're going.

52:24.142 --> 52:26.325
All right, so that leads to the last question.

52:26.885 --> 52:27.826
What's my part?

52:28.607 --> 52:30.769
Well, the key word here is commitment.

52:31.170 --> 52:34.253
Everything has been moving towards commitment.

52:34.273 --> 52:38.738
And in a non-committal city, I wanna call you to commit

52:38.914 --> 52:40.776
every single one of us.

52:41.557 --> 52:45.540
And I want to call you to commit or to recommit in three ways.

52:46.201 --> 52:49.684
So first, commit to follow Jesus.

52:50.585 --> 52:57.632
Listen, if you're here and you're not a Christian, I want to encourage you and challenge you to commit your life to Christ today.

52:58.393 --> 53:04.138
Maybe you've been seeking, maybe you've been on the fence, trust Him as Lord and Savior today.

53:04.499 --> 53:07.922
Christ died for you so that you could live for Him.

53:08.130 --> 53:10.913
There's nothing better in life, trusting Him today.

53:11.713 --> 53:18.921
And if you're a Christian, I wanna call you today to recommit your life to Jesus and build everything around Him.

53:19.361 --> 53:21.943
So first, commit to following Jesus.

53:22.004 --> 53:24.306
Second, commit to loving one another.

53:25.127 --> 53:27.669
We need Jesus and we need His family, the church.

53:28.450 --> 53:36.818
And if you're a Christian and you've been checking this church out or you've kind of been around but not really involved, I wanna call you today to commit to the church.

53:37.218 --> 53:41.082
And let me just explain what it means to be a member of the church.

53:41.883 --> 53:47.429
Scripture says that if you're a Christian, then you're a member of the family of God, the global church.

53:48.130 --> 53:53.475
But membership in the global church should be expressed in a commitment to a local church.

53:54.196 --> 54:03.506
In other words, local church membership is a shared commitment with a local body of believers to Christ, to one another, and a mission in the city.

54:04.194 --> 54:07.538
And so at Reality LA, we don't have people sign a contract.

54:07.799 --> 54:14.667
What we do is we verbally express our commitments together every year on Vision Sunday, which we'll do in just a bit.

54:15.428 --> 54:21.035
So today, I want to encourage you, commit to the church as an expression of your devotion to Christ.

54:21.616 --> 54:26.922
And if you've been a member of this church, maybe even for 20 years, recommit today.

54:26.962 --> 54:30.567
Don't just go through the motions, participate in the family of God.

54:30.727 --> 54:33.010
You belong in this community.

54:33.506 --> 54:36.689
And then third, in terms of commitment, commit to serve Los Angeles.

54:37.270 --> 54:41.254
We're here because God has called us here to represent him in this city.

54:41.815 --> 54:50.324
And so I want to encourage you to devote yourself to showing the love of Christ with your words and your deeds and your neighborhood and your workplace and throughout the city.

54:50.825 --> 54:52.326
And let's pray for Los Angeles.

54:52.386 --> 54:56.891
Let's pray for a powerful movement of God in this city that he loves so much.

54:57.552 --> 55:03.378
So that's the call to commit to Christ to one another and the city that he has called us to.

55:04.354 --> 55:12.182
Now, we're gonna respond today, but we're gonna do it in a way that's different than normal, but has become a tradition for us on Vision Sunday.

55:12.882 --> 55:17.327
I've tried to lay out who we are and where we're going, and now we're gonna respond in three ways.

55:18.147 --> 55:22.832
First, we'll receive communion because our commitment is first and foremost to Jesus.

55:23.773 --> 55:28.257
Second, we'll do a responsive reading as a way of expressing our commitment together.

55:28.297 --> 55:33.362
And then third, we're gonna pray, because for all this, we are completely dependent on God.

55:34.114 --> 55:37.117
And we're going to receive communion in a different way today.

55:38.018 --> 55:44.986
First, as a sign of our commitment to you as the people of this church, our elders are going to serve you communion today.

55:45.766 --> 55:48.950
So I want to invite our elders to go ahead and get in their places.

55:49.470 --> 55:53.194
I also want to invite the band to come on out and join me on stage.

55:53.995 --> 55:58.901
And in a minute, the elders will pass the plates so that you can get the elements for the Lord's Supper.

55:59.701 --> 56:03.986
Now, if you are a follower of Christ, take the bread and the cup and hold on to them.

56:04.098 --> 56:15.892
If you're not a Christian, we're so glad that you're here, but I would encourage you just to let the plates pass, not because you're unwelcome, but because this meal is a public declaration of faith in Christ.

56:16.833 --> 56:24.863
And then second, in terms of what's going to be different, as a sign of our unity in Christ, we're all going to receive communion together at the same time.

56:25.543 --> 56:27.826
So once you get communion, hold on to it.

56:28.546 --> 56:37.417
And then while we're serving communion, the band will be playing, and we're gonna have some scriptures on the screen that will be the basis for the response of reading that we're gonna do.

56:38.138 --> 56:45.767
We want you to reflect on these verses and consider if you can express your commitment to Christ and the church in those ways.

56:47.089 --> 56:47.189
Amen.

56:47.209 --> 56:57.682
All right, church family, as we transition into the Lord's Supper, I'm going to read a declaration over you all, and there are gonna be words on this screen that you will repeat after me, okay?

56:58.306 --> 57:12.559
So, beloved, the meal that we are about to take together is a celebration of Christ's victory, a reminder of His abundant grace to us, communion with His very self and hope of life everlasting.

57:14.641 --> 57:15.482
We come together.

57:27.894 --> 57:28.274
Amen.

57:28.738 --> 57:29.218
Let's pray.

57:31.280 --> 57:43.833
God, our good, good, good Father, senior Holy Spirit upon us, that the bread which we eat and the cup that we will drink may be to us a communion with the body and the blood of Christ.

57:45.074 --> 57:53.522
Father, grant that being joined together in Him, we may attain the unity of faith and grow up in every way into Christ our Lord.

57:54.062 --> 57:54.283
Amen.

57:55.544 --> 57:55.744
Amen.

57:55.764 --> 57:57.746
All right, the Lord Jesus,

57:57.826 --> 58:00.530
the same night that he was betrayed, took bread.

58:01.411 --> 58:06.598
And when he had given thanks, he broke it and gave it to them saying, take, eat.

58:07.539 --> 58:09.743
This is my body, which is given for you.

58:10.564 --> 58:12.667
Do this in remembrance of me.

58:13.928 --> 58:14.429
And we all ate.

58:22.140 --> 58:23.221
Amen.

58:23.241 --> 58:26.706
Now in the same way, he also took the cup after supper saying,

58:27.266 --> 58:29.610
This cup is the new covenant in my blood.

58:30.512 --> 58:34.440
Do this as often as you drink it and remembrance of me.

58:35.281 --> 58:36.083
And we all drink together.

58:40.451 --> 58:40.752
Amen.

58:41.653 --> 58:48.566
Now, beloved, as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until He comes.

58:48.867 --> 58:49.168
Amen.

58:50.009 --> 58:50.450
Amen.

58:58.530 --> 59:05.244
We will now affirm our mutual commitment to follow Jesus, love one another, and to serve Los Angeles.

59:06.527 --> 59:15.986
I will read the scripture over you, and if you are committed to the mission of the reality LA, we welcome you to read along the response on a screen marked congregation.

59:35.074 --> 59:42.361
And Jesus said to all, if anyone would come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross daily and follow me.

59:43.722 --> 59:51.229
By God's grace, we'll follow Jesus together, denying ourselves and trusting in him as Lord and Savior.

59:52.711 --> 59:57.796
The Lord says, just as I have loved you, you also ought to love one another.

59:58.737 --> 01:00:04.402
By this, all people will know that you are my disciples if you have love one for another.

01:00:05.442 --> 01:00:12.872
By God's grace, and as we receive God's love, we will love one another as members of the bodies of Christ.

01:00:14.334 --> 01:00:21.665
The Lord says, seek the welfare of the city where I have sent you into exile, and pray to the Lord on its behalf.

01:00:22.226 --> 01:00:24.989
For in its welfare, you will find your welfare.

01:00:26.271 --> 01:00:34.002
By God's grace, we will serve Los Angeles and pray on its behalf, knowing that God makes his appeal through us.

01:00:35.522 --> 01:00:43.092
These are waiting commitments, and the only way we will be able to keep them is by the grace of God and through the power of the Holy Spirit.

01:00:44.213 --> 01:00:44.554
Amen.

01:00:45.054 --> 01:00:52.263
Help us, Lord.

01:00:52.283 --> 01:00:53.365
Let's pray once more, Church.

01:00:57.290 --> 01:01:03.698
God, our Father almighty, we thank you for the abundant mercy that you have shown us in our Lord Jesus Christ.

01:01:04.802 --> 01:01:11.910
We've gathered here today to be reminded of that mercy, to be washed new in it, to be filled afresh with it.

01:01:13.151 --> 01:01:33.394
And so we ask by the power of your Holy Spirit that you would seal these commands and these commitments up in our hearts and help us to keep them in faithfulness all year long, remembering the glory of the gospel, that the moment we fail, we can turn to you and seek favor and you will give it in abundance.

01:01:33.794 --> 01:01:40.986
forgiving us, cleansing us, making us new and guiding us in your ways of righteousness now and forever.

01:01:41.827 --> 01:01:54.849
We ask that in this way, through our seeking to love and repent and serve and love again, you would make us more and more into the image of our Lord Jesus Christ for His glory and in His name.

01:01:55.330 --> 01:01:57.293
And everybody said, amen.

01:01:59.056 --> 01:02:00.018
Thank you for listening.

01:02:00.386 --> 01:02:04.722
For more audio and video content, please visit realityla.com.

